title: My device connected to E5336Bs-2&Bs-6’s wireless network, but cannot open Web UI
answer:
1. Double![](http://consumer.huawei.com/support/servlet/imageServlet?dlType=HtmlAreaImage&imageId=31536)to check your wireless network connection on windows start bar. Make sure your device is connected with your E5336Bs-2&Bs-6 not other Wi-Fi device. 

 2. Open Web Browser from your device (ex. Microsoft Internet Explorer). Go *<u>http://192.168.8.1</u>* to open E5336Bs-2&Bs-6’s Web UI. 

![](http://consumer.huawei.com/support/servlet/imageServlet?dlType=HtmlAreaImage&imageId=31537)


 3. If Web Browser failed to bring you to Web UI, click “Tool” from Browser then select “Internet Options”. 

  ![](http://consumer.huawei.com/support/servlet/imageServlet?dlType=HtmlAreaImage&imageId=31539) 

 Select “General” tab, then click “Delete Cookies”. 

 ![](http://consumer.huawei.com/support/servlet/imageServlet?dlType=HtmlAreaImage&imageId=31540) 

 Select “Connections” tab, then click “LAN settings”. 

  ![](http://consumer.huawei.com/support/servlet/imageServlet?dlType=HtmlAreaImage&imageId=31541) 

 For the “Local Area Network (LAN) Settings” pop-up, uncheck the top three check-boxes. Then click “OK” to apply changes. 

 ![](http://consumer.huawei.com/support/servlet/imageServlet?dlType=HtmlAreaImage&imageId=31542) 

 Refresh the Web Browser to show E5336Bs-2&Bs-6 management console page.
